The article is a statement by the President on National HIV Testing Day. The President emphasizes the importance of getting tested for HIV and highlights the progress made in research, prevention, and care for HIV/AIDS. The President mentions the release of a comprehensive plan for addressing the HIV/AIDS epidemic in the United States and the need to reduce new infections, increase access to care, and reduce health disparities related to HIV/AIDS. The President also highlights the fact that one in five Americans living with HIV are unaware of their infection, emphasizing the importance of knowing one's HIV status and getting into care. The President urges all Americans to join the fight against HIV/AIDS and get tested.